Section 10 Spring Data JPA CRUD Repositories
 Lecture 8: Create customer repository

1. Create new Repository Interface for the Customer
 1.1 Create new interface:
  - es.springframework.repositories.CustomerRepository.java
  - es.springframework.repositories.OrderRepository.java
  - es.springframework.repositories.ProductRepository.java
  - es.springframework.repositories.RoleRepository.java
  - es.springframework.repositories.UserRepository.java

2. Setup Repository Services
 2.1 Implements Interface:
  - es.springframework.reposervices.CustomerServiceRepoImpl.java
  ...... (refer to source code)
 2.2 Modify Role.java
  - Modify @ManyToMany annotation to @ManyToMany(fetch = FetchType.EAGER)

3. Setup the Spring Configuration
 3.1 Add Spring profile configuration in the src/main/resources/application.properties

4. Run and See the Results (Perhaps, it has some error...)

5. Refactoring ej.springframework.domain.User.java and ej.springframework.domain.security.Role.java
 5.1 Modify @ManyToMany annotation to @ManyTomay(fetch = FetchType.EAGER) in both of them

6. Re-Run Tomcat Server --> Go to localhost:8080/ --> select user --> Edit User data
